Project: Investigate a Dataset :- (TMDP-Movies)¶

The primary goal of the project is to go through the dataset and the general data analysis process using numpy, pandas and matplotlib. This contain four parts:¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Data Wrangling
  • Exploratory Data Analysis
  • Conclusions

Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue.I would like to find other intresting patterns in the dataset.

Question(s) for Analysis¶

1- What is the top (10) & low (10) movies bassed on the rating?

2- which year that has the most release movies and least?

3- The top and low profit movie?

4- What is the average popularity by generes?

5- Is there is a relation between this columns (vote average & popularity) , (release year & revenue & profit)?

Research Question 5:- Is there is a relation between this columns (vote average & popularity) , (release year & revenue & profit)¶

In [147]:
def FillPlot(df,xVar,yVar,PlotKind):
    
    
    # Plot the values
    df.plot(x=xVar,y=yVar,kind=PlotKind,figsize=(14,8))
    
    # Replace the (_) with a white space to fill the title & labels
    xVar = xVar.replace("_"," ")
    yVar = yVar.replace("_"," ")
    # Add the plot title and format it
    plt.title(f'Relationship between {xVar} and {yVar}'.title(), fontsize = 14, weight = "bold")
    # Add the xLabel and format it
    plt.xlabel(xVar.title(), fontsize = 14, weight = "bold")
    # Add the yLabel and format it
    plt.ylabel(yVar.title(), fontsize = 14, weight = "bold")

Conclusions¶

1- You can see the top(10) movies based on rating above also the lowest(10)

2- a) 2014 is the year with most release movies: 700

b) 1961 and 1969 are the lowest years of releasing movies: 31

3- a) The top profit movie is: avater with net profit = 2544505847

b) The lowest profit movie is: The Warrior's Way with net profit = -413912431

4- The most popular genres is adventure

5- The relation between the columns are positively relationships.

Limitations¶

The TMDB data set has alot of null values which could make the analysis isn't so accurate
